msgid "B</sbin/poweroff> [B<-n>] [B<-w>] [B<-d>] [B<-f>] [B<-i>] [B<-h>]"
msgstr "B</sbin/poweroff> [B<-n>] [B<-w>] [B<-d>] [B<-f>] [B<-i>] [B<-h>]"

#. type: Plain text
#: debian-bullseye debian-unstable
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "B<Halt> notes that the system is being brought down in the file B</var/"
#| "log/wtmp>, and then either tells the kernel to halt, reboot or poweroff "
#| "the system. If B<halt> or B<reboot> is called when the system is I<not> "
#| "in runlevel B<0> or B<6>, B<shutdown>(8) will be invoked instead (with "
#| "the flag B<-h> or B<-r>)."
msgid ""
"B<halt> notes that the system is being brought down in the file I</var/log/"
"wtmp>, and then either tells the kernel to halt, reboot or power-off the "
"system."
msgstr ""
"B<Halt> comprueba que el sistema está siendo desconectado en el archivo B</"
"var/log/wtemp>, y entonces llama al núcleo para detener, reiniciar o apagar "
"el sistema. Si se llama a B<halt> o B<reboot> cuando el sistema I<no> está "
"en los niveles B<0> o B<6>, será invocado B<shutdown>(8) (con el flag B<-h> "
"o B<-r>)."

#. type: Plain text
#: debian-bullseye debian-unstable
msgid ""
"If B<halt> or B<reboot> is called when the system is I<not> in runlevel B<0> "
"or B<6>, in other words when it's running normally, B<shutdown> will be "
"invoked instead (with the B<-h> or B<-r> flag). For more info see the "
"B<shutdown>(8)  manpage."
msgstr ""

